<P>
   JAPAN-POLITICS (Tokyo) _ Japan's Cabinet resigned en masse
Tuesday, setting the stage for a rapid political succession two
days after a life-threatening stroke incapacitated Prime Minister
Keizo Obuchi. Yoshiro Mori, secretary-general of governing party,
is expected to become prime minister on Wednesday. By Howard W.
French.
