<P>
   UGA-WRECK _ ATHENS, Ga. _ Oconee County and University of
Georgia officials continued their investigations into the death of
fraternity brother Benjamin Folsom Grantham III. The 20-year-old
student, who was handcuffed when he died in a car crash, graduated
from a private school in North Carolina and transferred to UGA from
Truett-McConnell College. County coroner said handcuffs made no
difference in his chances of survivng the crash. Greek Presidents
met Monday to warn against hazing and how to deal with the press in
the next few days. (McCarthy, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
