<P>
   EDITORS: Columbia News Service provides feature stories from the
New York City area every week for your use as desired. There is no
cost to you. CNS stories are transmitted courtesy of the New York
Times Syndicate/New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   The stories are slugged BC-CNS-keyword and move in the ``l''
news category. They are edited by adjunct professors who work at
The New York Times, Daily News, Newsday and The Associated Press,
among other places. The stories are written by degree candidates at
the Graduate School of Journalism at Columbia University. All we
ask is that you send us a tearsheet.
</P>
<P>
   So please, if you can, use our stories. Most of them are news
features that can be held until you have a pesky hole to fill.
</P>
