 &HT;    With MARCHES. For release Sunday, April 9.
 &HT;    c.2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   A MONTH OF MARCHES: THE DEMONSTRATION LINE-UP
</P>
<P>
   Mobilization for Global Justice
</P>
<P>
   When: April 16-17
</P>
<P>
   Why: Protest against economic and environmental policies
promoted by the World Bank and the International Monetary Fund.
Organizers vow to disrupt the spring trade meetings of the two
organizations.
</P>
<P>
   Who: Sponsors include labor unions and environmental activists.
</P>
<P>
   Web site: www. a16.org
</P>
<P>
   Earth Day 2000
</P>
<P>
   When: April 22
</P>
<P>
   Why: To promote clean energy, oppose pollution and arouse public
concern about environmental dangers such as global warming.
</P>
<P>
   Who: Sponsors include conservationists and environmental
activists. Leonardo DiCaprio will host a stage show featuring Clint
Black, Carole King, James Taylor and other entertainers. An
EarthFair will display hundreds of environmentally protective
projects.
</P>
<P>
   Web site: www.earthday.net
</P>
<P>
   Millennium March on Washington for Equality
</P>
<P>
   When: April 29-30
</P>
<P>
   Why: To promote gay and lesbian rights and mobilize supporters
for the November elections.
</P>
<P>
   Who: Sponsors include gay and lesbian rights organizations.
Melissa Etheridge, Garth Brooks, k.d. lang, and other singers will
perform at Equality Rocks, a concert Saturday, April 29. Ellen
DeGeneres, Anne Heche and other celebrities will lead a march and
rally on Sunday, April 30.
</P>
<P>
   Web site: www.mmow.org
</P>
<P>
   Million Mom March
</P>
<P>
   When: May 14 (Mother's Day)
</P>
<P>
   Why: To push Congress to pass gun control legislation.
</P>
<P>
   Who: The original organizer was Donna Dees-Thomases, a New
Jersey mother of two girls and stepmother of three sons and a
part-time TV public relations consultant. Sponsors include the Bell
Campaign, Handgun Control, Inc. and other groups advocating gun
control. Rosie O'Donnell will lead the march and preside over the
rally.
</P>
<P>
   Web site: www.millionmommarch.com
</P>
