   TECHNOLOGY
</P>
<P>
   TECH-CARRIERPOINT _ CarrierPoint, an Atlanta start-up using the
Internet to sell space on tractor-trailers, is set to announce next
week it is receiving a $22 million investment of venture capital. A
look at the company, the market and what they hope to do.
(Clothier, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   TECH-BATTERIES _ New electronic products are popping into the
marketplace like clockwork these days, but new radios, laptops and
wireless phones demand new battery products _ and that's what
Motorola Energy Systems Group provides. A visit to their new
facilities unveils a dazzling display of storage batteries, tiny
and large that range from self-charging units you can use marooned
in the jungle or powerful units that can run a notebook computer
for 11 hours straight. The metro Atlanta research and battery
production line are the flagship of Motorola's worldwide batter
production subsidiary. (Holsendolph, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
20. WITH PHOTO.
</P>
