attorneys general who act as equal partners in the case.
</P>
<P>
   Meantime, Assistant Attorney General Joel Klein, who heads the
Justice Department's antitrust division, sought to put the best
possible face on his team's disagreements with the attorneys
general, which Gates said had stymied the negotiations.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think, by and large, we have seen eye to eye on matters,''
Klein said. ``But at a given time, there may be some disagreements.
Honorable people, people of good faith, on occasion will find
that.''
</P>
<P>
   Jackson has told the plaintiffs privately that when the time
comes to suggest remedies he expects them to submit a unitary
brief.
</P>
<P>
   One person who does not expect new flexibility from Microsoft is
James Barksdale, the star government witness at the antitrust
trial, who accused Microsoft of seeking to illegally divide the
Internet market with Netscape Communications Corp., which has since
merged with America Online Inc.
</P>
<P>
   ``Microsoft should apologize for breaking the law,'' Barksdale
said. ``Instead, they've lost the basketball game by 110 points,
and all they can do is boast about the five field goals they
made,'' Barksdale said.
</P>
<P>
   ``You can't change the spots on this leopard,'' he concluded.
``I don't think they're evil people. I just don't think they
appreciate the law.''
</P>
<P>
   Andrew J. Glass's e-mail address is andyg(at)coxnews.com
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
