<P>
   TENN-EXECUTE (Atlanta) _ Two Tennessee inmates who were
scheduled to die this week in back-to-back executions received
last-minute reprieves Tuesday when a federal appellate court ruled
that more time was needed to review their cases. Robert Glen Coe,
convicted in the 1979 rape and murder of an 8-year-old girl, had
been scheduled to die at 1 a.m. Wednesday. Philip Ray Workman, who
was convicted of killing a Memphis police officer in 1981 while
fleeing a fast food restaurant he had just robbed, had been
scheduled to die 24 hours after Coe, at 1 a.m. Thursday. By Kevin
Sack.
