<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ Stock prices lurched dramatically Tuesday,
tumbling sharply during the morning and early afternoon but then
recovering and recouping much of the lost ground. The closing
averages were all moderately lower. But those numbers did not
adequately convey the degree of the swings during the session. And
traders said they did not reflect the pain and psychological damage
inflicted on investors. By Kenneth N. Gilpin.
</P>
