Imperato's family owns the oldest gun shop in New York City.
Growing up in Bensonhurt, Imperato said, he and his father, Louis,
never once went hunting. ``We didn't shoot at targets. None of our
hobbies ever involved guns. Guns were a job. Maybe the guys who run
Lobel's meat market are, you know, vegetarians. You never know.''
(Frances Roberts/The New York Times)
