<P>
   (NYT37) IGUALA, Mexico -- April 4, 2000 -- MEXICO-ENVIRON --
Rodolfo Montiel, 44, who organized a protest by peasants against
logging in the mountains north of Acapulco, at the federal
penitentiary at Iguala where he is being held pending trial on
drugs and weapons charges. But last Friday, Amnesty International
declared Montiel to be a prisoner of conscience. And on Wednesday,
a San Francisco foundation will award him with a $125,000
environmental prize. ``The only award I've gotten from the
government is prison, so I don't know quite what to think about
this prize from foreigners,'' he said. (Sam Dillon/The New York
Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT36) NEW YORK -- April 4, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN., APRIL 9 --
OM-PURI-FILMS -- Om Puri, in SoHo last month, plays a Pakistani
Muslim married to an Englishwoman in 1970s Manchester in ``East Is
East.'' Although Om Puri has appeared, by his own estimate, in
something like 140 films in his 24-year screen career and has been
characterized by one expert on Indian cinema as ``the finest actor
of the post-independence generation,'' he is still far from a
household name in the United States. (Suzanne DeChillo/The New York
Times)
