Gefilte Variations'' by Jayne Cohen. The book reveals the author's
frequently playful approach to Jewish food. Though there are riffs
on gefilte fish, including versions made with salmon and even one
using chicken, they are just one element in a book that reworks
typical Jewish cooking with improvisational flair. (Tony
